org.apache.jackrabbit.core.observation
Class EventConsumer

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.jackrabbit.core.observation.EventConsumer
class EventConsumer
extends Object

The EventConsumer class combines the EventListener with the implementation of specified filter for the listener: EventFilter.

Collections of EventState objects will be dispatched to consumeEvents(org.apache.jackrabbit.core.observation.EventStateCollection).

EventConsumer

EventConsumer(javax.jcr.Session session,
              javax.jcr.observation.EventListener listener,
              EventFilter filter)
An EventConsumer consists of a Session, the attached EventListener and an EventFilter.

Parameters:
session - the Session that created this EventConsumer.
listener - the actual EventListener to call back.
filter - only pass an Event to the listener if the EventFilter allows the Event.
Throws:
NullPointerException - if session, listener or filter isnull.

equals

public boolean equals(Object obj)
Returns true if this EventConsumer is equal to some other object, false otherwise.

Two EventConsumers are considered equal if they refer to the same Session and the EventListeners they reference are equal. Note that the EventFilter is ignored in this check.

Parameters:
obj - the reference object with which to compare.
Returns:
true if this EventConsumer is equal the other EventConsumer.
